The paper deals with real-time monitoring of power grids using deep neural networks. The subject matter falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY), which is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which makes it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of recurrent neural networks for forecasting also makes it relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the development of a novel model-specific DNN, which can be considered a software engineering problem, making it relevant to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
